25/05/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government Monday (24 May) approved the deployment of a new contingent to Iraq. 
The special operations unit, consisting of 32 troops, will be deployed from 1 June to 15 December. 
The United States will cover much of the cost.
Also Monday, Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski met with Pope John Paul II in Rome. 
They discussed efforts to strengthen interethnic confidence, coexistence and religious tolerance. 
The Pope said he hoped Macedonia would soon become part of a united Europe. 
(Dnevnik - 25/05/04; MIA, Makfax - 24/05/04)
